The paper deals with Markov decision processes (MDP), which are commonly studied in the subfield of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The concept of winning and optimal strategies is often studied in game theory (cs.GT), and the complexity analysis of decision problems is a common topic in logic and computation (cs.LO). The use of probability distributions and sequences of distributions suggests a connection to stochastic processes and data structures (cs.DS), while the application of strategies and decision-making aligns with artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
